headline: Fifth Third Bancorp (FITB): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q4 Earnings?
summary: Fifth Third Bancorp has had an impressive run over the past six months as its shares have beaten the S&P 500 by 18.6%. The stock now trades at $53.30, marking a 24.6% gain. This run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
